  "text": "Recent advances in deep learning have given rise to the use of sequence-to-sequence models (discriminative models) for speech recognition [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . In simple terms, sequence-to-sequence model for speech recognition takes an acoustic sequence as input and returns a transcript sequence as output [CITATION_3] .",
